<subSubSection id="DAF5444D0DF29F5033712A41F87D4C40" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ECDD333311D71446BA4EC58B62489E1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58106796D6AAED3E824B61259C4B2332" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName id="582E1097F35C28C68C0D3559189D86C4" class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis id="04512F45930C0DA7B3D3B1ED1D469DD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium sized species (11-12 mm). It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="FEAD9200B4BE75A9875855098E2DFC9F" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. calcaratus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis id="225796D21AF329AD9C5638838C977EC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4500A87D4D117BC5978B6575E9D2D870" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Antenna. A, B, J Merodon natans C, D, K M. pulveris E, F, I M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H-K female; A-H lateral view I-K dorsal view; A Greece (Olimp) B Greece (Achaia) C, D Turkey E, F, I Cyprus G, H Spain J Greece (Alexandroupoli) K Turkey. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576175" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">2C, D</figureCitation>
), broader metafemur in both sexes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A537C0583BF0D0AF72D5D254EC42142F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Metaleg without tarsomeres, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C, D M. pulveris E, F M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H female; A Italy (Sicily) B Croatia C, D Turkey E, F Cyprus G Algeria H Tunis. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576177" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">4C, D</figureCitation>
) and the large, rounded posterior surstyle lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DFA11166DF599D14A9100A331A3D41DB" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
) of the male genitalia (in 
<taxonomicName id="C98D2B89A665275D7C0EC742848A85EE" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. calcaratus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis id="B303CC0753535D094D61CE5F2D5FB5A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
narrow, fingerlike; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="092C52ED0FA0BD8947B118B2CB60DB42" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Merodon calcaratus epandrium, lateral view. A Morocco B, D Algeria C Tunis E left surstyle of specimen from Kenya F Kenya G Spain. Arrow marks invagination on ventral margin of surstyle. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576178" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">5A-G</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D3AC95E1AE45FF92470C2249DEA0011E" class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis id="F74ADECEB3160C556C9B24D3A10D29F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="7A3F9ADC7FDBDEB7AD2B1A298CE0531A" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis id="E94E18E52FBC6F816365AED0244F9D91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B11E923B723A59160C7E7E3632E81AC9" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis id="DD31695E97AF0C29727541EA7CD4579F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but differs by the following characters of the male genitalia: ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe with distinct triangular prominence (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="66C7BAF0A04B0E8D39013A3748994D95" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
:v), in 
<taxonomicName id="BD2F843D27408B246F160232921560B7" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis id="B9097FA62C3992CFBF82770FE997FEB5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without visible triangular prominence from lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C2AAC5127D1BECC4621A2BC21971D1E8" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10A, B</figureCitation>
), it can be present in some specimens, but it is small and visible only from ventral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D5381CB237AE22D24759BF823D9D7D48" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10A, B</figureCitation>
); posterior surstyle lobe broader and shorter (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6BE9923664ED3E8F415EE639025ED558" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
), narrower and more elongated in 
<taxonomicName id="A9945B37D1189F5C0229CF5C6DCBD8C7" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis id="B2E72834E9CB686F5E633283ADB3CE7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A3D122DC0323D9D3C3B3C36B9B9E40B5" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Merodon makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. male genitalia, Cyprus. A epandrium B left surstyle C, E hypandrium D aedeagus and associated structures; A, C, D lateral view B, E ventral view. Abbreviations: a - anterior surstyle lobe, aa - aedeagal apodeme, ae - aedeagus, c - cercus, ea - ejaculatory apodeme, la - lateral sclerite of aedeagus, n - notch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme, p - posterior surstyle lobe, v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576181" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">8A</figureCitation>
:p, B:p, 10D). Fossette position medially between the base of the arista and apex of basoflagellomere distinguishes females of this species from 
<taxonomicName id="871DB3F94DC37D09F49B1AA4B61AA57D" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis id="B43B2AFBB2E7DE42A52DDF7DA4F326F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov (in 
<taxonomicName id="7E3B6D2EB532F9D5EA112E1AE4D83264" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis id="D8EA07EBDA46052BA2D813EABD5D9645" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov position of fossette is near base of arista (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07C7CBA947884D9554A97F1EFFCAD679" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Antenna. A, B, J Merodon natans C, D, K M. pulveris E, F, I M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H-K female; A-H lateral view I-K dorsal view; A Greece (Olimp) B Greece (Achaia) C, D Turkey E, F, I Cyprus G, H Spain J Greece (Alexandroupoli) K Turkey. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576175" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">2I</figureCitation>
:f)). From 
<taxonomicName id="C8C659C6F0965A292149367910FAAD7B" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis id="F5A81866EBB219FEB5CECB3ACECEBA0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, females of 
<taxonomicName id="291E625C19E16851C2347B1A92854FF6" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis id="3CE71A6D2BC7B0BBCC7042077E88536E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by the presence of only yellow pile on the proleg tarsomeres, except in some specimens only, where the fifth tarsomere has sparse black pile (in 
<taxonomicName id="531303DB24E73E8747CA48F9A36E847A" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis id="3909BB8F210353EC3149B8AAEAC5F195" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proleg tarsomeres covered with yellow pile but also with some intermixed black pile).
</paragraph>
