<subSubSection id="D272D4BF795A924DDB04BFC1F43A3267" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AA51F8B94C4BD433ED87E8286E6DD9A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="83E09AB2E19194626F7E63C456415200" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName id="B48449DB92BFEB09BF43B93C85192422" class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis id="AE8AF000FA12D8531FAE245674398026" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the Anatolian Peninsula, the eastern Mediterranean islands (Lesvos, Samos, Rhodes) and Cyprus, but is absent from southern and western Europe as opposed to 
<taxonomicName id="89D4E12ED4B1C6575708EC788C807606" class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis id="324D2B0B7FE60E58C4CF0800005F981A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3BF4FEFDF102F17956BBF74D80C934F" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution map of the species of Merodon natans group." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576179" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB2C5518F0CE77782F18291179763C0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="96F6EF10DC843E26F253F1B90E7C5405" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E609303B56C3CBBA81D5299E9E2725D" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
Preferred environments (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1D8009C45E3B996A50ABE3A5B3608DB2" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Merodon pulveris. A male on Drimia aphylla, in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 6 Oct. 2016 B female in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 20 Oct. 2013 C typical habitat in Agiassos (Lesvos, Greece) where M. pulveris can be collected, photo: D. Vujanovic." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576185" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">12C</figureCitation>
) are open areas in Eastern European maquis on limestone near coniferous forests with large populations of its host plant 
<taxonomicName id="7485EAD22DA586EBB719B2E057CBC639" class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis id="72CCA52F81E6539AF7A3AA7B0FEFA658" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7B64E2B4848A009358E1F9929FF83A0B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" author="Radenkovic, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" pagination="35 - 56" refId="B47" refString="Radenkovic, S, Vujic, A, Stahls, G, Perez-Banon, C, Rojo, S, Petanidou, T, Simic, S, 2011. Three new cryptic species of the genus Merodon Meigen (Diptera: Syrphidae) from the island of Lesvos (Greece). Zootaxa 2735: 35 - 56, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" title="Three new cryptic species of the genus Merodon Meigen (Diptera: Syrphidae) from the island of Lesvos (Greece)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" volume="2735" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="6EFC90C8A868221916D38D440F31A63C" originalValue="Radenković">Radenkovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). Flowers visited include: 
<taxonomicName id="53F26A28649F22FCCC57722E61830959" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Foeniculum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Foeniculum" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D4409A589E54AB8B75A1C469212FBCDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Foeniculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName id="4AFE546CA68C0D5B10135E7D45038FA7" class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis id="A40A1DFEDC8F4CAA1CAFFF2C19E02332" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C93AF4F5679B0F542D23C7AD7F621FA4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" author="van Steenis, J" journalOrPublisher="Bonn zoological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" pagination="125 - 146" refId="B84" refString="van Steenis, J, van Zuijen, MP, van Steenis, W, Makris, C, van Eck, A, Mengual, X, 2019. Hoverflies (Diptera: Syrphidae) of Cyprus: results from a collecting trip in October 2017. Bonn zoological Bulletin 68 (1): 125 - 146, DOI: https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" title="Hoverflies (Diptera: Syrphidae) of Cyprus: results from a collecting trip in October 2017." url="https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" volume="68" year="2019">van Steenis et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="BABB83CD0F0565600F58C7FAC76EB0EC" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Drimia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Drimia aphylla" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aphylla">
<emphasis id="4CFDA124FDC2EF7AC4C5A86094E321AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Drimia aphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E123A59D61B296D09B0FED400312BF95" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Merodon pulveris. A male on Drimia aphylla, in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 6 Oct. 2016 B female in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 20 Oct. 2013 C typical habitat in Agiassos (Lesvos, Greece) where M. pulveris can be collected, photo: D. Vujanovic." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576185" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">12A</figureCitation>
). Flight period is in spring (April-May) and autumn (late September/mid October). The larva described here was found in 
<taxonomicName id="C8683803CC743C850CAE9A35431E03E7" class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis id="D6275BB913DEF1D82D3C729FBFD118C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Lesvos island in Greece.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
